    {"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Cultural Context"}],"depth":2,"type":"heading"},
    {"children":[{"type":"text","value":"碰 often describes chance encounters and unexpected situations in Chinese culture. The concept\nof 碰运气 (trying one's luck) reflects a pragmatic approach to uncertain situations. In daily\nconversation, 碰见 (bumping into someone) is a common way to describe unexpected meetings,\nemphasizing the accidental nature of many social encounters."}],"type":"paragraph"}
